      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix issue#95927:Install bug:No matching version found for node-domexception@1.0.28",
        "body": "\r\nCloses #95927\r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\nFixes an issue(https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/95927) where users cloning and installing OpenClaw from source would encounter a hard pnpm install failure due to an unresolvable node-domexception@1.0.28 dependency version, completely blocking the build and development workflow. This error is triggered when downloaded extensions include plugins that depend on gaxios (such as the Google Chat plugin), as this introduces gaxios@7.1.5 and pulls in the node-domexception sub-dependency chain for the first time.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\nAdds a _node-domexception:1.0.0_ override to the workspace root so that pnpm resolves the dependency to the existing 1.0.0 release, aligning with the 1.0.0 constraint already declared by fetch-blob. This fixes resolution failures triggered by gaxios-based plugins without upgrading fetch-blob or node-fetch, as both remain tied to the node-domexception 1.x line for CommonJS compatibility.\r\n\r\nAdd _'@napi-rs/wasm-runtime@1.1.6'_ in _./pnpm-workspace.yaml.minimumReleaseAgeExclude_ to avoid the follow error:\r\n`pnpm install\r\nScope: all 156 workspace projects\r\n✗ Lockfile failed supply-chain policy check (1361 entries in 17.3s)\r\n[ERR_PNPM_MINIMUM_RELEASE_AGE_VIOLATION] 1 lockfile entries failed verification:\r\n  @napi-rs/wasm-runtime@1.1.6 was published at 2026-06-24T07:22:04.062Z, within the minimumReleaseAge cutoff (2026-06-24T05:35:32.681Z)\r\n`\r\nThis error both happened on my machine and remote CI.\r\n\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\nUsers can now successfully install and build OpenClaw from source even when their selected extensions include plugins that depend on gaxios (such as the Google Chat plugin). Previously, this workflow would fail with an ERR_PNPM_NO_MATCHING_VERSION error when downloaded extensions include such plugins, blocking the build entirely; after this fix, pnpm install && pnpm build && pnpm ui:build completes cleanly regardless of such\r\nplugins are enabled.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\nbefore fixing:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1017\" height=\"313\" alt=\"2026-06-24_13-46\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f7a817e4-0ad1-4f2a-ae3e-a5d8920b4a00\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nafter fixing:\r\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile:\r\n<img width=\"907\" height=\"277\" alt=\"2026-06-25_09-57\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2d2c1345-8801-4d65-a3b8-050711129f57\" />\r\n\r\npnpm: build:\r\n<img width=\"1064\" height=\"361\" alt=\"2026-06-25_10-35\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06383eb3-01ff-4a13-bea3-c71664a71ec6\" />\r\n\r\npnpm: ui build:\r\n<img width=\"1033\" height=\"368\" alt=\"2026-06-25_10-49\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/59042e70-55fa-4b08-bfde-b811405a01e9\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Root Cause: Unresolvable node-domexception Dependency\r\n## Error\r\nScope: all 153 workspace projects\r\n✓ Lockfile passes supply-chain policies (1360 entries in 17s)\r\n[ERR_PNPM_NO_MATCHING_VERSION] No matching version found for node-domexception@1.0.28 while fetching it from https://registry.npmjs.org/\r\nThis error happened while installing the dependencies of @google/genai@2.7.0\r\nat google-auth-library@10.7.0\r\nat gaxios@7.1.5\r\nat node-fetch@3.3.2\r\nat fetch-blob@3.2.0\r\nThe latest release of node-domexception is \"2.0.2\".\r\n\r\n## History\r\nIssue https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/60338 was previously fixed by pinning node-domexception to 1.0.28 in package.json. That version is no longer available on the npm registry. The package has since been deprecated by its author; only four versions remain: 1.0.0, 2.0.0, 2.0.1, and 2.0.2.\r\n\r\n## Trigger\r\nThe error appears when downloaded extensions include plugins that depend on gaxios—such as the Google Chat plugin. The first install succeeds without these plugins. The second install pulls in gaxios@7.1.5, which introduces the node-fetch → fetch-blob → node-domexception chain for the first time.\r\n\r\n## Why Downgrade Is Not Viable\r\nfetch-blob@3.1.4 introduced the node-domexception requirement to fix a critical double-slice bug for filesystem-backed blobs. node-fetch@3.3.2 depends on fetch-blob@^3.1.4 specifically to include this fix. Downgrading either package would reintroduce the bug.\r\n\r\n## The Fix\r\nfetch-blob itself declares node-domexception: ^1.0.0. While 2.0.2 appears to work in local testing, it is ESM-only and may introduce compatibility issues with the CommonJS-based fetch-blob 3.x line. The safest resolution is to add node-domexception: 1.0.0 to pnpm-workspace.yaml, aligning with fetch-blob's own constraint. The package.json override was already removed from main in favor of workspace-level configuration, so pnpm-workspace.yaml is the correct location for this fix.\r\n\r\n## For the Review\r\nThe errors reported by ```Dependency Guard / dependency-guard (pull_request_target) ```  and ```CI / checks-node-compact-small-4 (pull_request)``` are triggered by the modification of the node-domexception version in this PR, and do not reflect actual critical problems.\r\n\r\nI'm also puzzled by the ```CI / check-shrinkwrap (pull_request) ``` failure. The command node scripts/generate-npm-shrinkwrap.mjs --all --check passes locally on my machine, but after pushing to the PR branch, GitHub CI fails with:\r\n`plain\r\nRun set -euo pipefail\r\n$ node scripts/generate-npm-shrinkwrap.mjs --all --check\r\ngenerated npm-shrinkwrap.json violates workspace overrides: node_modules/cliui locked 8.0.1, expected 6.0.0; node_modules/wrap-ansi locked 7.0.0, expected 6.2.0; node_modules/y18n locked 5.0.8, expected 4.0.3; node_modules/yargs-parser locked 21.1.1, expected 18.1.3\r\n[ELIFECYCLE] Command failed with exit code 1.\r\nError: Process completed with exit code 1.`\r\nAnd here is my pass evidence on my machine:\r\n<img width=\"1010\" height=\"871\" alt=\"2026-06-26_09-16\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/24cacdf0-ccd1-482d-8fdc-2ee07093051e\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nThe updates to the test .ts files were made to accommodate the node-domexception version adjustment. The remaining changes are solely to align with the upstream main branch. However, these appear to have been misidentified by clawsweeper as unrelated updates authored by me.",
